        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Society of the &#34;United Hebrew Charities&#34;<lb/>
                636. N. 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Str.<lb/></p>
            <p>Philada Sept 10th 1888<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                City.<lb/>
                Reverend Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>Owing to the increasing demand<lb/> upon the resources of this Institution&#44;<lb/> having already overdrawn our Treasury<lb/> to the amount of about <hi rend="underline">&#36;3000</hi> arising<lb/> from the necessities of the growing tide<lb/> of Immigrants&#44; coupled with the wants&#44;<lb/> who already are and continue to be<lb/> beneficiaries of this Society&#44; it is the<lb/> hope of the Board of Government&#44; that<lb/> recognizing the increasing demands<lb/> of our need Coreligionists the amounts<lb/> contributed for the current year will be<lb/> larger in proportion&#44; as the demand upon<lb/> our resources grow greater.<lb/></p>
            <p>You will permit me therefore&#44; to request<lb/></p>
            
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>you to make an urgent appeal to<lb/> the Members of your Congregation in your<lb/> Sermon on Yom Kippur&#44; that they may<lb/> assist this Charity liberally and to their<lb/> fullest extent.<lb/></p>
            <p>Thanking you sincerely in the<lb/> name of the Board of the Government<lb/> in anticipation of your kind efforts in<lb/> the divine cause of Charity<lb/></p>
            <p>I have the honor to be<lb/>
                very Obediently Yours<lb/>
                David Klein<lb/>
                Secretary<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
